Step 1: Read in .idat files and save rgset objects as .Rdata file

File input comes from 2 different directories:

  1. /home/datasets/EPIC/setA

  2. /home/datasets/EPIC/yangivana_72_11142017

File output will go here:

To run this on lead server use: R -e "rmarkdown::render('/home/woodche/ECHO/processing_PLC_MSC_methlyation/code/01_QC_PLC_MSC.Rmd',output_file='/home/woodche/ECHO/processing_PLC_MSC_methlyation/code/01_QC_PLC_MSC.html')"

QC Steps

  1. Removal of samples with low median intensity (1 sample removed)

  2. Removal of probes with a detection p-value greater than 0.01 in more than 10% of samples (866,836 probes removed)

  3. Removal of samples with a detection p-value greater than 0.01 in more than 1% of probes (0 samples removed)

  4. Removal of probes with a bead count <3 in at least 5% of samples (9,438 probes removed)

  5. Non-CG probes were assessed, but were not removed (2,928 non-CG probes kept)

  6. Non-mapping probes were assessed (0 non-mapping probes)

  7. Removal of probes with SNPs at the CpG interrogation and/or at the single nucleotide extension for any minor allele frequency (29,809 probes removed)

  8. Removal of cross-reactive probes (40,655 probes removed). The list of known cross-reactive probes came from the papers by Pidsley et al. (Critical evaluation of the Illumina MethylationEPIC BeadChip microarray for whole-genome DNA methylation profiling. Genome Biology (2016)) and McCartney et al. (Identification of polymorphic and off-target probe binding sites on the Illumina Infinium MethylationEPIC BeadChip. Genomics Data (2016))

  9. Removal of samples with mis-matched sex between the clinical data and predicted sex through the minfi getSex function (2 samples removed)

Quality Control (preform on the tissues together)

Outlier Identification

Outliers will be identified as samples that are under the 1st percentile for median methlyated intensity or greater than the 99th percentile for the fraction of failed positions. If a sample is identified as an outlier in the methylated median intensity and fraction of failed positions then it was removed.

Find cell composition of Placenta Data
# function from cran page of minfi 
projectCellType <- function(Y, coefCellType, contrastCellType = NULL,
                            nonnegative = TRUE, lessThanOne = FALSE) {
    if (is.null(contrastCellType)) {
        Xmat <- coefCellType
    } else {
        Xmat <- tcrossprod(coefCellType, contrastCellType)
    }

    nCol <- dim(Xmat)[2]
    if (nCol == 2) {
        Dmat <- crossprod(Xmat)
        mixCoef <- t(
            apply(Y, 2, function(x) solve(Dmat, crossprod(Xmat, x))))
        colnames(mixCoef) <- colnames(Xmat)
        return(mixCoef)
    } else {
        nSubj <- dim(Y)[2]

        mixCoef <- matrix(0, nSubj, nCol)
        rownames(mixCoef) <- colnames(Y)
        colnames(mixCoef) <- colnames(Xmat)

        if (nonnegative) {
            if (lessThanOne) {
                Amat <- cbind(rep(-1, nCol), diag(nCol))
                b0vec <- c(-1, rep(0, nCol))
            } else {
                Amat <- diag(nCol)
                b0vec <- rep(0, nCol)
            }
            for (i in seq_len(nSubj)) {
                obs <- which(!is.na(Y[,i]))
                Dmat <- crossprod(Xmat[obs,])
                mixCoef[i,] <- solve.QP(
                    Dmat = Dmat,
                    dvec = crossprod(Xmat[obs,], Y[obs,i]),
                    Amat = Amat,
                    bvec = b0vec)$sol
            }
        } else {
            for (i in seq_len(nSubj)) {
                obs <- which(!is.na(Y[,i]))
                Dmat <- crossprod(Xmat[obs,])
                mixCoef[i,] <- solve(Dmat, t(Xmat[obs,]) %*% Y[obs,i])
            }
        }
        mixCoef
    }
}

quant_norm <- function(gset_clean, tissue){
  gset_norm <- preprocessQuantile(gset_clean, removeBadSamples = T)
  beta_norm <- getBeta(gset_norm)
  colnames(beta_norm) <- sampleNames(gset_clean)
  m_norm <- getM(gset_norm)
  colnames(m_norm) <- sampleNames(gset_clean)
  
  totalProbes <- dim(beta_norm)[1]

  # Plot density of norm beta
  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "normBeta_", tissue, ".jpg"))
  main1 <- bquote("Density plot of Normalized "~beta~"("*.(totalProbes)~"probes)")
  pal = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2")
  densityPlot(beta_norm, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Plate,
              main = main1, xlab = expression(beta), legend=F)
  legend("top", legend = levels(as.factor(pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Plate)), text.col = pal)
  invisible(dev.off())
  
  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "mds_infantSex_", tissue, ".jpg"), width = 960)
  par(cex = 0.8, mfrow = c(1,2))
  mdsPlot(beta_norm, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$infant_sex, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, main = "Whole Genome: MDS Infant Sex, beta")
  mdsPlot(m_norm, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$infant_sex, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, main = "Whole Genome: MDS Infant Sex, m-value")
  invisible(dev.off())
  
  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "mds_samplePlate_", tissue, ".jpg"), width = 960)
  par(cex = 0.8, mfrow = c(1,2))
  mdsPlot(beta_norm, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Plate, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, main = "Whole Genome: MDS Sample Plate, beta")
  mdsPlot(m_norm, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Plate, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, main = "Whole Genome: MDS Sample Plate, m-value")
  invisible(dev.off())
  
  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "mds_array_", tissue, ".jpg"), width = 960)
  par(cex = 0.8, mfrow = c(1,2))
  mdsPlot(beta_norm, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Array, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, main = "Whole Genome: MDS Array, beta")
  mdsPlot(m_norm, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Array, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, main = "Whole Genome: MDS Array, m-value")
  invisible(dev.off())

    # look at the autosomes 
  annotation <- getAnnotation(gset_norm)
  autosomes <- annotation[!annotation$chr %in% c("chrX", "chrY"),]
  gset_norm_auto <- gset_norm[featureNames(gset_norm) %in% row.names(autosomes),]
  beta_norm_auto <- getBeta(gset_norm_auto)
  m_norm_auto    <- getM(gset_norm_auto)
  colnames(m_norm_auto) <- sampleNames(gset_norm)
  totalProbes2 <- dim(beta_norm_auto)[1]

  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "normBeta_auto_", tissue, ".jpg"))
  main1 <- bquote("Autosomes: Density plot of Normalized"~beta~"("*.(totalProbes2)~"probes)")
  pal = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2")
  densityPlot(beta_norm_auto, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Plate,
              main = main1, xlab = expression(beta), legend=F)
  legend("top", legend = levels(as.factor(pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Plate)), text.col = pal)
  invisible(dev.off())
  
  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "mds_infantSex_auto_", tissue, ".jpg"), width = 960)
  par(cex = 0.8, mfrow = c(1,2))
  mdsPlot(beta_norm_auto, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm_auto)$infant_sex, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Name, main = "Autosomes: MDS Infant Sex, beta")
  mdsPlot(m_norm_auto, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm_auto)$infant_sex, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Name, main = "Autosomes: MDS Infant Sex, m-value")
  invisible(dev.off())

  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "mds_samplePlate_auto_", tissue, ".jpg"), width = 960)
  par(cex = 0.8, mfrow = c(1,2))
  mdsPlot(beta_norm_auto, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Plate, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Name, main = "Autosomes: MDS Sample Plate, beta")
  mdsPlot(m_norm_auto, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Plate, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Name, main = "Autosomes: MDS Sample Plate, m-value")
  invisible(dev.off())
  
  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "mds_array_auto_", tissue, ".jpg"), width = 960)
  par(cex = 0.8, mfrow = c(1,2))
  mdsPlot(beta_norm_auto, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Array, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Name, main = "Autosomes: MDS Array, beta")
  mdsPlot(m_norm_auto, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Array, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm_auto)$Sample_Name, main = "Autosomes: MDS Array, m-value")
  invisible(dev.off())
  
  out <- list(gset_norm, beta_norm, m_norm, gset_norm_auto, beta_norm_auto, m_norm_auto)
  names(out) <- c("gset", "beta", "mset", "auto_gset", "auto_beta", "auto_mset")
  
  return(out)
}

Batch Correction

batch_cor <- function(gset_norm, beta_norm, m_norm, tissue){
  mod <- model.matrix(~1, data = pData(gset_norm))
  
  # by Plate
  m_norm_plate <- ComBat(m_norm, gset_norm$Sample_Plate, mod, par.prior = TRUE, prior.plots = FALSE)
  colnames(m_norm_plate) <- sampleNames(gset_norm)
  beta_norm_plate <- lumi::m2beta(m_norm_plate)
  
  getPalette <- colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"))
  
  # plot Plate
  ncolor <- length(unique(pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Plate))
  jpeg(paste0(fig_ext, "mds_normPlate_", tissue, ".jpg"), width = 960)
  par(cex = 0.4, mfrow = c(1,2))
  mdsPlot(beta_norm_plate, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Plate, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, pal = getPalette(ncolor),
          main = "Whole Genome, Plate Corrected: MDS Plate, beta values")
  mdsPlot(m_norm_plate, numPositions = 1000, sampGroups = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Plate, 
          sampNames = pData(gset_norm)$Sample_Name, pal = getPalette(ncolor),
          main = "Whole Genome, Plate Corrected: MDS Plate, m-values")
  invisible(dev.off())
  
  out <- list(beta_norm_plate, m_norm_plate)
  names(out) <- c("beta", "m")
  return(out)
}

end_PLC <- batch_cor(norm_PLC$gset, norm_PLC$beta, norm_PLC$mset, "PLC")
end_MSC <- batch_cor(norm_MSC$gset, norm_MSC$beta, norm_MSC$mset, "MSC")
